- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with computing M-ellipsoids of convex bodies, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents a deterministic algorithm for estimating the volume of a convex body, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper discusses improved deterministic algorithms for fundamental lattice problems under general norms, which involves numerical computations.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper mentions a known lower bound for computing M-ellipsoids, which involves analyzing the computational complexity of the problem.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with estimating the volume of a convex body, which can be viewed as a problem in information theory.
